            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Research from email platform providers suggests STO can lift open rates by 3-15% compared to a fixed send time. However, the impact varies significantly by list size, industry, and email platform quality. STO works best when your subscribers have consistent, learnable email habits. For small or new lists without enough historical data, results are often negligible.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Which email platforms offer send time optimization?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Major platforms offering STO (under various names) include: Mailchimp (Send Time Optimization), Klaviyo (Smart Send Time), HubSpot (Smart Email Scheduling), ActiveCampaign (Predictive Sending), Campaign Monitor (Send Time Optimization), and Brevo/Sendinblue (Send Time Optimization). Implementation quality and minimum list size requirements vary by platform.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How much historical data is needed for STO to work?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
